aWFRuleDesc.RuleDescription:
Eligibility based on insurance age; Must be between 18 and 64, or 18 and 59 if WOP
Eg. Suppose John's policy anniversary date is Dec 31, 2010 and John's birth date is June 30, 1940, then John's Age is 60 years and 184 days at policy anniversary. So, the Owner Age in this case will be considered as 61 instead of 60 at anniversary. In case John's birthday had happened to be 180 days of within his policy's anniversary date, then the Owner Age will be considered to be 60 years. Simply put, if John was born on July 05, 1940, his age at anniversary would still be considered as 60 instead of 61 as in the earlier case.
aWFRuleDesc.RuleText:
; aWF_RT_Formule (aWLI_LifeDisabilityRuleEngine) (Def Version:2) (Implem Version:1)
type tWF_Generated_WaiverofPremium_318773432_20 : (IsWaiverofPremium, IsNotWaiverofPremium)
function Contract__Classifications__WaiverofPremium return tWF_Generated_WaiverofPremium_318773432_20 if self.EvaluateClassificationFromRank(0, 1, 'Contract__Classifications__WaiverofPremium') _Result = tWF_Generated_WaiverofPremium_318773432_20(self.V_ForClassificationEvaluation) endIf endFunc
procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : Boolean) Result = (self.Insured__Age__At_Last_Renewal >= 18) and (self.Insured__Age__Nearest_At_Last_Renewal <= 64) if Result = False self.AppendComment(self.Msg('0006')) endIf if (Result = True) and (self.Contract__Classifications__WaiverofPremium = IsWaiverofPremium) Result = (self.Insured__Age__At_Last_Renewal >= 18) and (self.Insured__Age__Nearest_At_Last_Renewal <= 59) if Result = False self.AppendComment('Insured Age must be between 18 and 59 to choose WOP') endIf endIf endProc

function TenYearTermLifeRates(InsuredAmount : Num8, InsuredAge : Int4, Healthclass : tWF_Generated_HealthClass_318774001_7, Gender : tWF_Generated_UsedForRules_Gender_318774001_3, Smoker : tWF_Generated_Smoker_318774281_4) return tWFNum8 uses aWFStandAloneRule

tmpRule = self.GetExactRuleToExecuteFromRankInRuleDesc(0, self.CurrentDate) if tmpRule <> Nil aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(InsuredAmount, 0, tmpRule) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(InsuredAge, 1, tmpRule) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(Healthclass, 2, tmpRule) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(Gender, 3, tmpRule) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(Smoker, 4, tmpRule) tmpRule.GetStandAloneResult(_Result, self) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).CleanParamsAfterExecution(tmpRule) else self.AppendComment('No rule version defined at this date') endIf endFunc
function TenYearWaiverofPremiumRates(Gender : tWF_Generated_UsedForRules_Gender_318774001_3, InsuredAge : Int4) return tWFNum8 uses aWFStandAloneRule
var tmpRule : aWFRuleDesc
tmpRule = self.GetExactRuleToExecuteFromRankInRuleDesc(1, self.CurrentDate) if tmpRule <> Nil aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(Gender, 0, tmpRule) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(InsuredAge, 1, tmpRule) tmpRule.GetStandAloneResult(_Result, self) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).CleanParamsAfterExecution(tmpRule) else self.AppendComment('No rule version defined at this date') endIf endFunc

procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : tWFNum8) var WOPPremium : Num8
; if self.Insured__Gender = gMale Result = self.TenYearTermLifeRates(self.Option__CoverageAmount, self.Insured__Age__Nearest_At_Last_Renewal, self.Option__Classifications__HealthClass, Male, self.Insured__Classifications__Smoker) else Result = self.TenYearTermLifeRates(self.Option__CoverageAmount, self.Insured__Age__Nearest_At_Last_Renewal, self.Option__Classifications__HealthClass, Female, self.Insured__Classifications__Smoker) endIf ; self.AppendBillLineDetail(Result, 'Base Rate') ; if self.Contract__Classifications__WaiverofPremium = IsWaiverofPremium if self.Insured__Gender = gMale Result = Result * self.TenYearWaiverofPremiumRates(Male, self.Insured__Age__Nearest_At_Last_Renewal) else Result = Result * self.TenYearWaiverofPremiumRates(Female, self.Insured__Age__Nearest_At_Last_Renewal) endIf self.AppendBillLineDetail(WOPPremium, 'WOP Rate') endIf endProc

aWFRuleDesc.RuleDescription:
Insured up to 75. Age calculated based on insurance age.
Eg. Suppose John's policy anniversary date is Dec 31, 2010 and John's birth date is June 30, 1940, then John's Age is 60 years and 184 days at policy anniversary. So, the Owner Age in this case will be considered as 61 instead of 60 at anniversary. In case John's birthday had happened to be 180 days of within his policy's anniversary date, then the Owner Age will be considered to be 60 years. Simply put, if John was born on July 05, 1940, his age at anniversary would still be considered as 60 instead of 61 as in the earlier case.
aWFRuleDesc.RuleText:
; aWF_RT_Formule (aWLI_LifeDisabilityRuleEngine) (Def Version:2) (Implem Version:1)
uses WFTypes, aWFDateType
procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : tWFDate) var birthdate : tWFDate var nearestDate : tWFDate var age : Int4
birthdate = self.Insured__BirthDate Result = self.Option__SubscriptionDate nearestDate = Result self.IncMonths(6, nearestDate) age = nearestDate.type.GetNbYearsDifference(birthdate, nearestDate) ; while age < 75 self.IncYears(1, Result) nearestDate = Result self.IncMonths(6, nearestDate) age = nearestDate.type.GetNbYearsDifference(birthdate, nearestDate) endWhile endProc

aWFRuleDesc.RuleText:
; aWF_RT_Formule (aWLI_LifeDisabilityRuleEngine) (Def Version:1) (Implem Version:1)
procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : Num8) if self.Option__CoverageAmount * 0.7 <= 250000 if (self.Claim__ExactCost <= self.Option__CoverageAmount * 0.7) and (self.Claim__ExactCost >= 10000) Result = self.Claim__ExactCost elseif self.Claim__ExactCost < 10000 Result = 10000 elseif self.Claim__ExactCost > self.Option__CoverageAmount * 0.7 Result = self.Option__CoverageAmount * 0.7 endIf elseif (self.Option__CoverageAmount * 0.7 > 250000) and (self.Claim__ExactCost > 250000) Result = 250000 elseif (self.Option__CoverageAmount * 0.7 > 250000) and (self.Claim__ExactCost <= 250000) Result = self.Claim__ExactCost endIf endProc

aWFRuleDesc.RuleDescription: The insured must be between 18 and 64. We are not considering his exact age at subscription, but his age minus and plus 6 months. Eg. Suppose John's policy anniversary date is Dec 31, 2010 and John's birth date is June 30, 1940, then John's Age is 60 years and 184 days at policy anniversary. So, the Owner Age in this case will be considered as 61 instead of 60 at anniversary. In case John's birthday had happened to be 180 days of within his policy's anniversary date, then the Owner Age will be considered to be 60 years. Simply put, if John was born on July 05, 1940, his age at anniversary would still be considered as 60 instead of 61 as in the earlier case.
aWFRuleDesc.RuleText:
; aWF_RT_Formule (aWLI_LifeDisabilityRuleEngine) (Def Version:2) (Implem Version:1)
procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : Boolean) Result = (self.Insured__Age__Nearest_At_Last_Renewal >= 18) and (self.Insured__Age__Nearest_At_Last_Renewal <= 64) if Result = False self.AppendComment('Insured Age must be between 18 and 64') endIf endProc

aWFRuleDesc.RuleDescription: A base rate is calculated based on some tables If WOP has been subscribed, a coefficient is then added
aWFRuleDesc.RuleText:
; aWF_RT_Formule (aWLI_LifeDisabilityRuleEngine) (Def Version:2) (Implem Version:1)
uses aWFRuleDesc, WFTypes, aWFStandardPerson
type tWF_Generated_Gender_318773432_4 : (Male, Female) type tWF_Generated_WaiverofPremium_318773432_20 : (IsWaiverofPremium, IsNotWaiverofPremium)
function TenYearAccidentalDeathBenefitRates(InsuredAge : Int4, Gender : tWF_Generated_Gender_318773432_4) return Num8 uses aWFStandAloneRule
var tmpRule : aWFRuleDesc
tmpRule = self.GetExactRuleToExecuteFromRankInRuleDesc(0, self.CurrentDate) if tmpRule <> Nil aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(InsuredAge, 0, tmpRule) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(Gender, 1, tmpRule) tmpRule.GetStandAloneResult(_Result, self) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).CleanParamsAfterExecution(tmpRule) else self.AppendComment('No rule version defined at this date') endIf endFunc
function TenYearWaiverofPremiumRates(Gender : tWF_Generated_Gender_318773432_4, InsuredAge : Int4) return Num8 uses aWFStandAloneRule
var tmpRule : aWFRuleDesc
tmpRule = self.GetExactRuleToExecuteFromRankInRuleDesc(1, self.CurrentDate) if tmpRule <> Nil aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(Gender, 0, tmpRule) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(InsuredAge, 1, tmpRule) tmpRule.GetStandAloneResult(_Result, self) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).CleanParamsAfterExecution(tmpRule) else self.AppendComment('No rule version defined at this date') endIf endFunc
function Contract__Classifications__WaiverofPremium return tWF_Generated_WaiverofPremium_318773432_20 if self.EvaluateClassificationFromRank(2, 1, 'Contract__Classifications__WaiverofPremium') _Result = tWF_Generated_WaiverofPremium_318773432_20(self.V_ForClassificationEvaluation) endIf endFunc
procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : tWFNum8) var TableRate : Num8 var WOPPremium : Num8
TableRate = self.TenYearAccidentalDeathBenefitRates(self.Insured__Age__Nearest_At_Last_Renewal, Male) if self.Insured__Gender = gMale Result = self.TenYearAccidentalDeathBenefitRates(self.Insured__Age__Nearest_At_Last_Renewal, Male) else Result = self.TenYearAccidentalDeathBenefitRates(self.Insured__Age__Nearest_At_Last_Renewal, Female) endIf ; self.AppendBillLineDetail(TableRate, 'Base Rate') Result = TableRate if self.Contract__Classifications__WaiverofPremium = IsWaiverofPremium if self.Insured__Gender = gMale WOPPremium = self.TenYearWaiverofPremiumRates(Male, self.Insured__Age__Nearest_At_Last_Renewal) Result += Result * WOPPremium else WOPPremium = self.TenYearWaiverofPremiumRates(Female, self.Insured__Age__Nearest_At_Last_Renewal) Result += Result * WOPPremium endIf self.AppendBillLineDetail(WOPPremium, 'WOP Rate') endIf endProc

aWFRuleDesc.RuleDescription:
The person is eligible up to 64. We are looking at his age at policy anniversary date. And we check his age based on insurance age.
Eg. Suppose John's policy anniversary date is Dec 31, 2010 and John's birth date is June 30, 1940, then John's Age is 60 years and 184 days at policy anniversary. So, the Owner Age in this case will be considered as 61 instead of 60 at anniversary. In case John's birthday had happened to be 180 days of within his policy's anniversary date, then the Owner Age will be considered to be 60 years. Simply put, if John was born on July 05, 1940, his age at anniversary would still be considered as 60 instead of 61 as in the earlier case.
aWFRuleDesc.RuleText:
; aWF_RT_Formule (aWLI_LifeDisabilityRuleEngine) (Def Version:2) (Implem Version:1)
uses WFTypes, aWFDateType
procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : tWFDate) var birthdate : tWFDate var nearestDate : tWFDate var age : Int4
birthdate = self.Insured__BirthDate Result = self.Option__SubscriptionDate nearestDate = Result nearestDate.type.IncMonths(6, @nearestDate) age = nearestDate.type.GetNbYearsDifference(birthdate, nearestDate) ; while age < 64 Result.type.IncYears(1, @Result) nearestDate = Result nearestDate.type.IncMonths(6, @nearestDate) age = nearestDate.type.GetNbYearsDifference(birthdate, nearestDate) endWhile endProc
